        rightContent: "<b>Chapter 6: A Cry That Heaven Heard</b>\n\nTime in heaven had no hours, no nights. Grief existed only in depth.\n\nShe could hold it no longer. Her broken sob echoed across the luminous expanse like thunder — not heard as sound, but as wound.\n\nSomewhere down on Earth, her mother clutched her daughter’s photograph, shivering from exhaustion, yet still begging for justice. Their worlds were connected by suffering, yet separated by fate.\n\nHer cry had not changed God, but it stirred the space around her. A soft glow began forming behind her — hesitant, warm, inviting. Someone else had heard her.\n"
