        rightContent: "<b>Chapter 8: A Story of Flames</b>\n\n“I was once a cheerful girl,” the second spirit began. “My parents loved me. At nineteen, I was married off for dowry. In-laws tortured me, humiliated me, and when I resisted… they burned me alive. My so-called husband defamed my father while planning a second marriage. I survived the flames, but not completely — my innocence, my trust, my hope, were all burned.”\n\nThe first spirit felt her sorrow twist and mingle with this story. Their grief, though different, mirrored the cruelty of a world blind to suffering.\n\n“I wish Earth could be a place where women walk without fear,” the second spirit whispered. “Where mothers protect their children without begging for mercy.”\n"
