        rightContent: "<b>Chapter 10: If Heaven Could Speak</b>\n\nThey looked down at Earth, a world cruel and blind, where mothers wept for daughters stolen too soon, and injustice walked freely.\n\n“We cannot change their world,” said the second spirit, “but we can exist in truth. And maybe, if enough souls remember, the cries that were ignored may awaken justice.”\n\nThe first spirit nodded. “We bear witness — for our mothers, for children, for those who cannot speak. We may not bring justice, but we will not allow the world to forget.”\n\nHeaven pulsed with quiet understanding. No answers were given. No words spoken. And yet, in the shared presence of two wounded souls, there was recognition, affirmation, and the faintest glimmer of peace.\n\nThey would never forget. They would never forgive Earth entirely. But they would endure.\n\nBecause even in a world that had failed them, and even in heaven’s silence, truth remained unbroken.\n"
